IR tools Collection

All in one Tools

     * [https://belkasoft.com/ec]Belkasoft Evidence Center - The toolkit
       will quickly extract digital evidence from multiple sources by
       analyzing hard drives, drive images, memory dumps, iOS, Blackberry
       and Android backups, UFED, JTAG and chip-off dumps
     * [https://github.com/PowerShellMafia/CimSweep]CimSweep - CimSweep is
       a suite of CIM/WMI-based tools that enable the ability to perform
       incident response and hunting operations remotely across all
       versions of Windows
     * [https://github.com/byt3smith/CIRTKit]CIRTkit - CIRTKit is not just
       a collection of tools, but also a framework to aid in the ongoing
       unification of Incident Response and Forensics investigation
       processes
     * [http://www.cybertriage.com/]Cyber Triage - Cyber Triage remotely
       collects and analyzes endpoint data to help determine if it is
       compromised. It's agentless approach and focus on ease of use and
       automation allows companies to respond without major infrastructure
       changes and without a team of forensics experts. Its results are
       used to decide if the system should be erased or investigated
       further.
     * [http://www.arxsys.fr/discover/]Digital Forensics Framework - DFF
       is an Open Source computer forensics platform built on top of a
       dedicated Application Programming Interface (API). DFF proposes an
       alternative to the aging digital forensics solutions used today.
       Designed for simple use and automation, the DFF interface guides
       the user through the main steps of a digital investigation so it
       can be used by both professional and non-expert to quickly and
       easily conduct a digital investigations and perform incident
       response
     * [https://github.com/mwielgoszewski/doorman]Doorman - Doorman is an
       osquery fleet manager that allows remote management of osquery
       configurations retrieved by nodes. It takes advantage of osquery's
       TLS configuration, logger, and distributed read/write endpoints, to
       give administrators visibility across a fleet of devices with
       minimal overhead and intrusiveness
     * [https://github.com/mephux/envdb]Envdb - Envdb turns your
       production, dev, cloud, etc environments into a database cluster
       you can search using osquery as the foundation. It wraps the
       osquery process with a (cluster) node agent that can communicate
       back to a central location
     * [https://github.com/CrowdStrike/falcon-orchestrator]Falcon
       Orchestrator - Falcon Orchestrator by CrowdStrike is an extendable
       Windows-based application that provides workflow automation, case
       management and security response functionality.
     * [https://github.com/google/grr]GRR Rapid Response - GRR Rapid
       Response is an incident response framework focused on remote live
       forensics. It consists of a python agent (client) that is installed
       on target systems, and a python server infrastructure that can
       manage and talk to the agent
     * [https://kolide.com/fleet]Kolide Fleet - Kolide Fleet is a state of
       the art host monitoring platform tailored for security experts.
       Leveraging Facebook's battle-tested osquery project, Kolide
       delivers fast answers to big questions.
     * [https://github.com/refractionpoint/limacharlie]Limacharlie - an
       endpoint security platform. It is itself a collection of small
       projects all working together, and gives you a cross-platform
       (Windows, OSX, Linux, Android and iOS) low-level environment
       allowing you to manage and push additional modules into memory to
       extend its functionality
     * [http://mig.mozilla.org/]MIG - Mozilla Investigator (MIG) is a
       platform to perform investigative surgery on remote endpoints. It
       enables investigators to obtain information from large numbers of
       systems in parallel, thus accelerating investigation of incidents
       and day-to-day operations security
     * [https://github.com/mozilla/MozDef]MozDef - The Mozilla Defense
       Platform (MozDef) seeks to automate the security incident handling
       process and facilitate the real-time activities of incident
       handlers
     * [https://github.com/biggiesmallsAG/nightHawkResponse]nightHawk -
       the nightHawk Response Platform is an application built for
       asynchronus forensic data presentation using ElasticSearch as the
       backend. It's designed to ingest Redline collections.
     * [http://sourceforge.net/projects/ocfa/]Open Computer Forensics
       Architecture - Open Computer Forensics Architecture (OCFA) is
       another popular distributed open-source computer forensics
       framework. This framework was built on Linux platform and uses
       postgreSQL database for storing data
     * [https://osquery.io/]Osquery - with osquery you can easily ask
       questions about your Linux and OSX infrastructure. Whether your
       goal is intrusion detection, infrastructure reliability, or
       compliance, osquery gives you the ability to empower and inform a
       broad set of organizations within your company. Queries in the
       incident-response pack help you detect and respond to breaches
     * [https://www.fireeye.com/services/freeware/redline.html]Redline -
       provides host investigative capabilities to users to find signs of
       malicious activity through memory and file analysis, and the
       development of a threat assessment profile
     * [http://www.sleuthkit.org/]The Sleuth Kit & Autopsy - The Sleuth
       Kit is a Unix and Windows based tool which helps in forensic
       analysis of computers. It comes with various tools which helps in
       digital forensics. These tools help in analyzing disk images,
       performing in-depth analysis of file systems, and various other
       things
     * [https://thehive-project.org/]TheHive - TheHive is a scalable
       3-in-1 open source and free solution designed to make life easier
       for SOCs, CSIRTs, CERTs and any information security practitioner
       dealing with security incidents that need to be investigated and
       acted upon swiftly.
     * [http://www.x-ways.net/forensics/]X-Ways Forensics - X-Ways is a
       forensics tool for Disk cloning and imaging. It can be used to find
       deleted files and disk analysis
     * [https://github.com/zentralopensource/zentral]Zentral - combines
       osquery's powerful endpoint inventory features with a flexible
       notification and action framework. This enables one to identify and
       react to changes on OS X and Linux clients.

Books

     * [https://medium.com/@sroberts/introduction-to-dfir-d35d5de4c180/]Df
       ir intro - By Scott J. Roberts
     * [http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1593275099]The Practice of
       Network Security Monitoring: Understanding Incident Detection and
       Response - Richard Bejtlich's book on IR

Communities

     * [https://augmentd.co/]augmentd - Community driven site provididing
       a list of searches that can be implemented in and executed with a
       variety of common security tools.
     * [https://lists.sans.org/mailman/listinfo/dfir]Sans DFIR mailing
       list - Mailing list by SANS for DFIR
     * [https://dfircommunity.slack.com/]Slack DFIR channel - Slack DFIR
       Communitiy channel - [https://rishi28.typeform.com/to/sTbTI8]Signup
       here

Disk Image Creation Tools

     * [http://accessdata.com/product-download/?/support/adownloads#FTKIma
       ger]AccessData FTK Imager - AccessData FTK Imager is a forensics
       tool whose main purpose is to preview recoverable data from a disk
       of any kind. FTK Imager can also acquire live memory and paging
       file on 32bit and 64bit systems
     * [https://github.com/vitaly-kamluk/bitscout]Bitscout - Bitscout by
       Vitaly Kamluk helps you build your fully-trusted customizable
       LiveCD/LiveUSB image to be used for remote digital forensics (or
       perhaps any other task of your choice). It is meant to be
       transparent and monitorable by the owner of the system,
       forensically sound, customizable and compact.
     * [http://www.forensicimager.com/]GetData Forensic Imager - GetData
       Forensic Imager is a Windows based program that will acquire,
       convert, or verify a forensic image in one of the following common
       forensic file formats
     * [http://guymager.sourceforge.net/]Guymager - Guymager is a free
       forensic imager for media acquisition on Linux
     * [https://www.magnetforensics.com/magnet-acquire/]Magnet ACQUIRE -
       ACQUIRE by Magnet Forensics allows various types of disk
       acquisitions to be performed on Windows, Linux, and OS X as well as
       mobile operating systems.

Evidence Collection

     * [https://github.com/simsong/bulk_extractor]bulk_extractor -
       bulk_extractor is a computer forensics tool that scans a disk
       image, a file, or a directory of files and extracts useful
       information without parsing the file system or file system
       structures. Because of ignoring the file system structure, the
       program distinguishes itself in terms of speed and thoroughness
     * [https://github.com/rough007/CDQR]Cold Disk Quick Response - uses a
       streamlined list of parsers to quickly analyze a forenisic image
       file (dd, E01, .vmdk, etc) and output nine reports
     * [https://github.com/diogo-fernan/ir-rescue]ir-rescue - ir-rescue is
       a Windows Batch script and a Unix Bash script to comprehensively
       collect host forensic data during incident response.
     * [https://www.brimorlabs.com/tools/]Live Response Collection - The
       Live Response collection by BriMor Labs is an automated tool that
       collects volatile data from Windows, OSX, and *nix based operating
       systems

Incident Management

     * [https://www.cybercpr.com/]CyberCPR - A community and commercial
       incident management tool with Need-to-Know built in to support GDPR
       compliance while handling sensitive incidents
     * [https://www.cyphon.io/]Cyphon - Cyphon eliminates the headaches of
       incident management by streamlining a multitude of related tasks
       through a single platform. It receives, processes and triages
       events to provide an all-encompassing solution for your analytic
       workflow -- aggregating data, bundling and prioritizing alerts, and
       empowering analysts to investigate and document incidents.
     * [https://www.demisto.com/product/]Demisto - Demisto community
       edition(free) offers full Incident lifecycle management, Incident
       Closure Reports, team assignments and collaboration, and many
       integrations to enhance automations (like Active Directory,
       PagerDuty, Jira and much more...)
     * [https://github.com/certsocietegenerale/FIR/]FIR - Fast Incident
       Response (FIR) is an cybersecurity incident management platform
       designed with agility and speed in mind. It allows for easy
       creation, tracking, and reporting of cybersecurity incidents and is
       useful for CSIRTs, CERTs and SOCs alike
     * [https://www.bestpractical.com/rtir/]RTIR - Request Tracker for
       Incident Response (RTIR) is the premier open source incident
       handling system targeted for computer security teams. We worked
       with over a dozen CERT and CSIRT teams around the world to help you
       handle the ever-increasing volume of incident reports. RTIR builds
       on all the features of Request Tracker
     * [http://getscot.sandia.gov/]SCOT - Sandia Cyber Omni Tracker (SCOT)
       is an Incident Response collaboration and knowledge capture tool
       focused on flexibility and ease of use. Our goal is to add value to
       the incident response process without burdening the user
     * [https://github.com/defpoint/threat_note]threat_note - A
       lightweight investigation notebook that allows security researchers
       the ability to register and retrieve indicators related to their
       research

Linux Distributions

     * [https://forensics.cert.org/#ADIA]ADIA - The Appliance for Digital
       Investigation and Analysis (ADIA) is a VMware-based appliance used
       for digital investigation and acquisition and is built entirely
       from public domain software. Among the tools contained in ADIA are
       Autopsy, the Sleuth Kit, the Digital Forensics Framework,
       log2timeline, Xplico, and Wireshark. Most of the system maintenance
       uses Webmin. It is designed for small-to-medium sized digital
       investigations and acquisitions. The appliance runs under Linux,
       Windows, and Mac OS. Both i386 (32-bit) and x86_64 (64-bit)
       versions are available.
     * [http://www.caine-live.net/index.html]CAINE - The Computer Aided
       Investigative Environment (CAINE) contains numerous tools that help
       investigators during their analysis, including forensic evidence
       collection
     * [https://github.com/rough007/CCF-VM]CCF-VM - CyLR CDQR Forensics
       Virtual Machine (CCF-VM): An all-in-one solution to parsing
       collected data, making it easily searchable with built-in common
       searches, enable searching of single and multiple hosts
       simultaneously
     * [http://www.deftlinux.net/]DEFT - The Digital Evidence & Forensics
       Toolkit (DEFT) is a Linux distribution made for computer forensic
       evidence collection. It comes bundled with the Digital Advanced
       Response Toolkit (DART) for Windows. A light version of DEFT,
       called DEFT Zero, is also available, which is focused primarily on
       forensically sound evidence collection
     * [https://sourceforge.net/projects/nst/files/latest/download?source=
       files]NST - Network Security Toolkit - Linux distribution that
       includes a vast collection of best-of-breed open source network
       security applications useful to the network security professional
     * [https://sumuri.com/software/paladin/]PALADIN - PALADIN is a
       modified Linux distribution to perform various forenics task in a
       forensically sound manner. It comes with many open source forensics
       tools included
     * [https://github.com/Security-Onion-Solutions/security-onion]Securit
       y Onion - Security Onion is a special Linux distro aimed at network
       security monitoring featuring advanced analysis tools
     * [http://digital-forensics.sans.org/community/downloads]SIFT
       Workstation - The SANS Investigative Forensic Toolkit (SIFT)
       Workstation demonstrates that advanced incident response
       capabilities and deep dive digital forensic techniques to
       intrusions can be accomplished using cutting-edge open-source tools
       that are freely available and frequently updated

Linux Evidence Collection

     * [https://github.com/SekoiaLab/Fastir_Collector_Linux]FastIR
       Collector Linux - FastIR for Linux collects different artefacts on
       live Linux and records the results in csv files

Log Analysis Tools

     * [https://github.com/jensvoid/lorg]Lorg - a tool for advanced HTTPD
       logfile security analysis and forensics
     * [https://github.com/dogoncouch/logdissect]Logdissect - A CLI
       utility and Python API for analyzing log files and other data.

Memory Analysis Tools

     * [https://github.com/JamesHabben/evolve]Evolve - Web interface for
       the Volatility Memory Forensics Framework
     * [https://github.com/ShaneK2/inVtero.net]inVtero.net - Advanced
       memory analysis for Windows x64 with nested hypervisor support
     * [http://www.gmgsystemsinc.com/knttools/]KnTList - Computer memory
       analysis tools
     * [https://github.com/504ensicsLabs/LiME]LiME - LiME (formerly DMD)
       is a Loadable Kernel Module (LKM), which allows the acquisition of
       volatile memory from Linux and Linux-based devices
     * [https://www.fireeye.com/services/freeware/memoryze.html]Memoryze -
       Memoryze by Mandiant is a free memory forensic software that helps
       incident responders find evil in live memory. Memoryze can acquire
       and/or analyze memory images, and on live systems, can include the
       paging file in its analysis
     * [https://www.fireeye.com/services/freeware/memoryze-for-the-mac.htm
       l]Memoryze for Mac - Memoryze for Mac is Memoryze but then for
       Macs. A lower number of features, however
     * [http://www.rekall-forensic.com/]Rekall - Open source tool (and
       library) for the extraction of digital artifacts from volatile
       memory (RAM) samples
     * [http://www.countertack.com/responder-pro]Responder PRO - Responder
       PRO is the industry standard physical memory and automated malware
       analysis solution
     * [https://github.com/volatilityfoundation/volatility]Volatility - An
       advanced memory forensics framework
     * [https://github.com/mkorman90/VolatilityBot]VolatilityBot -
       VolatilityBot is an automation tool for researchers cuts all the
       guesswork and manual tasks out of the binary extraction phase, or
       to help the investigator in the first steps of performing a memory
       analysis investigation
     * [https://github.com/aim4r/VolDiff]VolDiff - Malware Memory
       Footprint Analysis based on Volatility
     * [http://www.windowsscope.com/index.php?page=shop.product_details&fl
       ypage=flypage.tpl&product_id=35&category_id=3&option=com_virtuemart
       ]WindowsSCOPE - another memory forensics and reverse engineering
       tool used for analyzing volatile memory. It is basically used for
       reverse engineering of malwares. It provides the capability of
       analyzing the Windows kernel, drivers, DLLs, virtual and physical
       memory

Memory Imaging Tools

     * [http://belkasoft.com/ram-capturer]Belkasoft Live RAM Capturer - A
       tiny free forensic tool to reliably extract the entire content of
       the computer's volatile memory - even if protected by an active
       anti-debugging or anti-dumping system
     * [https://github.com/halpomeranz/lmg/]Linux Memory Grabber - A
       script for dumping Linux memory and creating Volatility profiles.
     * [https://www.magnetforensics.com/free-tool-magnet-ram-capture/]Magn
       et RAM Capture - Magnet RAM Capture is a free imaging tool designed
       to capture the physical memory of a suspect's computer. Supports
       recent versions of Windows
     * [http://www.osforensics.com/]OSForensics - OSForensics can acquire
       live memory on 32bit and 64bit systems. A dump of an individual
       process's memory space or physical memory dump can be done

OSX Evidence Collection

     * [https://github.com/synack/knockknock]Knockknock - Displays
       persistent items(scripts, commands, binaries, etc.) that are set to
       execute automatically on OSX
     * [https://github.com/ydkhatri/mac_apt]mac_apt - macOS Artifact
       Parsing Tool - Plugin based forensics framework for quick mac
       triage that works on live machines, disk images or individual
       artifact files
     * [https://github.com/jipegit/OSXAuditor]OSX Auditor - OSX Auditor is
       a free Mac OS X computer forensics tool
     * [https://github.com/yelp/osxcollector]OSX Collector - An OSX
       Auditor offshoot for live response

Other Lists

     * [https://github.com/deralexxx/security-apis]List of various
       Security APIs - A collective list of public JSON APIs for use in
       security.

Other Tools

     * [https://thehive-project.org/]Cortex - Cortex allows you to analyze
       observables such as IP and email addresses, URLs, domain names,
       files or hashes one by one or in bulk mode using a Web interface.
       Analysts can also automate these operations using its REST API.
     * [https://crits.github.io/]Crits - a web-based tool which combines
       an analytic engine with a cyber threat database
     * [https://github.com/diogo-fernan/domfind]domfind - domfind is a
       Python DNS crawler for finding identical domain names under
       different TLDs.
     * [https://github.com/TryCatchHCF/DumpsterFire]DumpsterFire - The
       DumpsterFire Toolset is a modular, menu-driven, cross-platform tool
       for building repeatable, time-delayed, distributed security events.
       Easily create custom event chains for Blue Team drills and sensor /
       alert mapping. Red Teams can create decoy incidents, distractions,
       and lures to support and scale their operations.
     * [https://github.com/Neo23x0/Fenrir]Fenrir - Fenrir is a simple IOC
       scanner. It allows scanning any Linux/Unix/OSX system for IOCs in
       plain bash. Created by the creators of THOR and LOKI
     * [https://github.com/keithjjones/fileintel]Fileintel - Pull
       intelligence per file hash
     * [https://github.com/Cyb3rWard0g/HELK]HELK - Threat Hunting platform
     * [https://github.com/obsidianforensics/hindsight]Hindsight -
       Internet history forensics for Google Chrome/Chromium
     * [https://github.com/keithjjones/hostintel]Hostintel - Pull
       intelligence per host
     * [https://github.com/ralphje/imagemounter]imagemounter - Command
       line utility and Python package to ease the (un)mounting of
       forensic disk images
     * [https://github.com/davehull/Kansa/]Kansa - Kansa is a modular
       incident response framework in Powershell
     * [https://github.com/aboutsecurity/rastrea2r]rastrea2r - allows one
       to scan disks and memory for IOCs using YARA on Windows, Linux and
       OS X
     * [https://raqet.github.io/]RaQet - RaQet is an unconventional remote
       acquisition and triaging tool that allows triage a disk of a remote
       computer (client) that is restarted with a purposely built forensic
       operating system
     * [https://www.percona.com/doc/percona-toolkit/2.2/pt-stalk.html]Stal
       k - Collect forensic data about MySQL when problems occur
     * [https://github.com/jadacyrus/searchgiant_cli]SearchGiant - a
       commandline utility to acquire forensic data from cloud services
     * [https://github.com/google/stenographer]Stenographer - Stenographer
       is a packet capture solution which aims to quickly spool all
       packets to disk, then provide simple, fast access to subsets of
       those packets. It stores as much history as it possible, managing
       disk usage, and deleting when disk limits are hit. It's ideal for
       capturing the traffic just before and during an incident, without
       the need explicit need to store all of the network traffic
     * [https://github.com/0x4d31/sqhunter]sqhunter - a threat hunter
       based on osquery and Salt Open (SaltStack) that can issue ad-hoc or
       distributed queries without the need for osquery's tls plugin.
       sqhunter allows you to query open network sockets and check them
       against threat intelligence sources.
     * [https://github.com/CIRCL/traceroute-circl]traceroute-circl -
       traceroute-circl is an extended traceroute to support the
       activities of CSIRT (or CERT) operators. Usually CSIRT team have to
       handle incidents based on IP addresses received. Created by
       Computer Emergency Responce Center Luxembourg
     * [https://www.raymond.cc/blog/xray/]X-Ray 2.0 - A Windows utility
       (poorly maintained or no longer maintained) to submit virus samples
       to AV vendors

Playbooks

     * [https://www.demisto.com/category/playbooks/]Demisto Playbooks
       Collection - Playbooks collection
     * [https://github.com/certsocietegenerale/IRM]IRM - Incident Response
       Methodologies by CERT Societe Generale
     * [https://www.incidentresponse.com/playbooks/]IR Workflow Gallery -
       Different generic incident response workflows, e.g. for malware
       outbreak, data theft, unauthorized access,... Every workflow
       constists of seven steps: prepare, detect, analyze, contain,
       eradicate, recover, post-incident handling. The workflows are
       online available or for download
     * [https://response.pagerduty.com/]PagerDuty Incident Response
       Documentation - Documents that describe parts of the PagerDuty
       Incident Response process. It provides information not only on
       preparing for an incident, but also what to do during and after.
       Source is available on
       [https://github.com/PagerDuty/incident-response-docs]GitHub.

Process Dump Tools

     * [http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=4060]Micro
       soft User Mode Process Dumper - The User Mode Process Dumper
       (userdump) dumps any running Win32 processes memory image on the
       fly
     * [http://www.ntsecurity.nu/toolbox/pmdump/]PMDump - PMDump is a tool
       that lets you dump the memory contents of a process to a file
       without stopping the process

Sandboxing/reversing tools

     * [https://github.com/cuckoobox]Cuckoo - Open Source Highly
       configurable sandboxing tool
     * [https://github.com/spender-sandbox/cuckoo-modified]Cuckoo-modified
       - Heavily modified Cuckoo fork developed by community
     * [https://github.com/keithjjones/cuckoo-modified-api]Cuckoo-modified
       -api - A Python library to control a cuckoo-modified sandbox
     * [https://www.hybrid-analysis.com/]Hybrid-Analysis - Hybrid-Analysis
       is a free powerful online sandbox by Payload Security
     * [https://malwr.com/]Malwr - Malwr is a free online malware analysis
       service and community, which is powered by the Cuckoo Sandbox
     * [https://github.com/KoreLogicSecurity/mastiff]Mastiff - MASTIFF is
       a static analysis framework that automates the process of
       extracting key characteristics from a number of different file
       formats
     * [https://www.metadefender.com/]Metadefender Cloud - Metadefender is
       a free threat intelligence platform providing multiscanning, data
       sanitization and vulnerability assesment of files
     * [https://github.com/viper-framework/viper]Viper - Viper is a python
       based binary analysis and management framework, that works well
       with Cuckoo and YARA
     * [https://www.virustotal.com/]Virustotal - Virustotal, a subsidiary
       of Google, is a free online service that analyzes files and URLs
       enabling the identification of viruses, worms, trojans and other
       kinds of malicious content detected by antivirus engines and
       website scanners
     * [https://github.com/keithjjones/visualize_logs]Visualize_Logs -
       Open source visualization library and command line tools for logs.
       (Cuckoo, Procmon, more to come...)

Timeline tools

     * [https://www.fireeye.com/services/freeware/highlighter.html]Highlig
       hter - Free Tool available from Fire/Mandiant that will depict
       log/text file that can highlight areas on the graphic, that
       corresponded to a key word or phrase. Good for time lining an
       infection and what was done post compromise
     * [https://github.com/etsy/morgue]Morgue - A PHP Web app by Etsy for
       managing postmortems.
     * [https://github.com/log2timeline/plaso]Plaso - a Python-based
       backend engine for the tool log2timeline
     * [https://github.com/google/timesketch]Timesketch - open source tool
       for collaborative forensic timeline analysis

Videos

     * [https://www.demisto.com/category/videos/]Demisto IR video
       resources - Video Resources for Incident Response and Forensics
       Tools
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bDcx4UNpKNc]The Future of Incident
       Response - Presented by Bruce Schneier at OWASP AppSecUSA 2015

Windows Evidence Collection

     * [https://github.com/OMENScan/AChoir]AChoir - Achoir is a
       framework/scripting tool to standardize and simplify the process of
       scripting live acquisition utilities for Windows
     * [http://binaryforay.blogspot.co.il/p/software.html]Binaryforay -
       list of free tools for win forensics
       ([http://binaryforay.blogspot.co.il/]http://binaryforay.blogspot.co
       .il/)
     * [http://www.crowdstrike.com/community-tools/]Crowd Response - Crowd
       Response by CrowdStrike is a lightweight Windows console
       application designed to aid in the gathering of system information
       for incident response and security engagements. It features
       numerous modules and output formats
     * [https://github.com/SekoiaLab/Fastir_Collector]FastIR Collector -
       FastIR Collector is a tool that collects different artefacts on
       live Windows systems and records the results in csv files. With the
       analyses of these artefacts, an early compromise can be detected
     * [https://github.com/jipegit/FECT]FECT - Fast Evidence Collector
       Toolkit (FECT) is a light incident response toolkit to collect
       evidences on a suspicious Windows computer. Basically it is
       intended to be used by non-tech savvy people working with a
       journeyman Incident Handler
     * [https://github.com/rabbitstack/fibratus]Fibratus - tool for
       exploration and tracing of the Windows kernel
     * [https://www.fireeye.com/services/freeware/ioc-finder.html]IOC
       Finder - IOC Finder is a free tool from Mandiant for collecting
       host system data and reporting the presence of Indicators of
       Compromise (IOCs). Support for Windows only
     * [https://www.fidelissecurity.com/resources/fidelis-threatscanner]Fi
       delis ThreatScanner - Fidelis ThreatScanner is a free tool from
       Fidelis Cybersecurity that uses OpenIOC and YARA rules to report on
       the state of an endpoint. The user provides OpenIOC and YARA rules
       and executes the tool. ThreatScanner measures the state of the
       system and, when the run is complete, a report for any matching
       rules is generated. Windows Only.
     * [https://github.com/Neo23x0/Loki]LOKI - Loki is a free IR scanner
       for scanning endpoint with yara rules and other indicators(IOCs)
     * [https://github.com/AlmCo/Panorama]Panorama - Fast incident
       overview on live Windows systems
     * [https://github.com/Invoke-IR/PowerForensics]PowerForensics - Live
       disk forensics platform, using PowerShell
     * [https://github.com/gfoss/PSRecon/]PSRecon - PSRecon gathers data
       from a remote Windows host using PowerShell (v2 or later),
       organizes the data into folders, hashes all extracted data, hashes
       PowerShell and various system properties, and sends the data off to
       the security team. The data can be pushed to a share, sent over
       email, or retained locally
     * [https://code.google.com/p/regripper/wiki/RegRipper]RegRipper -
       Regripper is an open source tool, written in Perl, for
       extracting/parsing information (keys, values, data) from the
       Registry and presenting it for analysis
     * [https://code.google.com/p/triage-ir/]TRIAGE-IR - Triage-IR is a IR
       collector for Windows

